<TITLE> Dhaka residents must be more 'aware' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 6 (bdnews24.com)Dhaka dwellers have no other way but to be "aware" if they want to save their lives, a senior minister has said. At a discussion on Sunday, organised by the government to observe the 'World Environment Day', agriculture minister Matia Chowdhury said the incidents at Begunbari and Nimtali were signs of danger. "So everyone should correct their previous mistakes from now ," she told the meeting at Bangabandhu Avenue. "Otherwise, nature will take its revenge and we will not be able to escape." "Illegal encroachment on rivers and water bodies must be stopped to keep the overall environment friendly," Matia stressed. State minister for forest and environment Hassan Mahmud also spoke at the meeting. A cultural programme following the discussion was postponed honouring the dead at Nimtali tragedy. bdn
